com.github.crashdemons.playerheads.api

Interface HeadDisplay

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CustomHead, PHHeadType

    public interface HeadDisplay
    Interface defining display details (names and appearance) of heads which are not used in their identity / comparison.
    Since:
    5.3.0-SNAPSHOT
    Author:
    crashdemons (crashenator at gmail.com)

    • Method Summary

      @NotNull String getDisplayName()

      • getDisplayName

        @NotNull
@NotNull String getDisplayName()
        Gets the item displayname for the associated skulltype, as defined in the "lang" file. Originally directly part of HeadType until 5.3

        A string containing the skulltype's displayname

      • getTexture

@NotNull String getTexture()

      • getLore

        @Nullable
@Nullable List<String> getLore()
        gets the head's special loretext (item description) to display for the item. If this is null, the default PlayerHeads loretext will be used (if applicable) instead.
        Returns:
        list of loretext lines to override the loretext, or null for default.
